
*Git Credential Manager Core* (GCM Core) simplifies → Microsoft/Azure/products/DevOps/authentication[authentication] with
→ Microsoft/Azure/products/Repos Git repositories

Git Credential Manager Core comes with → development/version-control-systems/git/Windows.

In order to provide a consistent authentication expierence across multiple platforms, GCM Core replaces
  • the .NET Framework-based Git Credential Manager for Windows (GCM),
  • and the Java-based Git Credential Manager for Mac and Linux (Java GCM)

GCM Core provides multi-factor authentication support for
  • → Microsoft/Azure/products/DevOps
  • Azure DevOps Server (formerly Team Foundation Server)
  • → development/version-control-systems/git/github
  • Bitbucket.

GCM Core is built on → Microsoft/dot-net/implementations/Core and runs on Windows and macOS. As of 2021-02, Linux is supported in an early preview.

sa:
  The → development/version-control-systems/git/options[Git option] `credential.helper`.
